The water pet does not do 100 dps consitantly, nevermind 125 dps. The water pet, positioned by a melee, with all mage buffs will do much closer to 85 dps counting backstab,  melee, nukes, and procs. Sometimes it gets lucky roles and will do over 100 dps, but every time that happens it gets unlucky roles and wont reach 70 dps. On boss mobs under those outlined conditions, this figure is much closer to 50, maybe 60 dps.<br>
<br>
Let me quote you from a summary of damage i took on acidic mass, the ros boss regarding mage vs beastlord damage. This was a 14 minute fight. Please note that this beastlord is a guildie so his gear is realtively similar to mine:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>MAGES</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Noonie</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> - 74,286 (87 dps, based on total log time)<br>
Kenantik - 27,790 (32.77 dps, based on its uptime)<br>
Pet nukes (80 hits @ 140, assumed a 20% resist rate) - 8,960 (10.56 dps based on its uptime)<br>
Pet weapon procs (22 hits @ 140, assumed a 20% resist rate) - 2,464 (2.9 dps)<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Total damage: 113,500 (about 133.23 dps)</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>BEASTLORDS</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Otubok</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> - 26,953 (31.71 dps based on his uptime)<br>
Otubok's procs (40 hits @ 150, assumed a 10% resist rate) - 5,400 (6.53 dps based on his uptime)<br>
Otubok's nukes (59 hits @ 450, assumed a 10% resist rate) - 23,895 (28.01 dps based on total log time)<br>
Warder (unknown buffs/pet type, imbued with blizzard) - 27,101 (34.74 dps based on its uptime)<br>
Warder's procs (35 hits @ 132, assumed a 20% resist rate) - 3,696 (4.73 dps)<br>
Warder's weapon procs (about 12 hits @ 140, assumed a 20% resist rate) - 1,344 (1.72 dps)<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Total damage: 91,447 (about 112.17 dps)</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->&quot;<br>
